<tr>
    <td  bgcolor="#000080"><FONT color="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;Subject:&nbsp;What Happened to Us On Hate Raid</font></td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td  bgcolor="#DCDCDC" valign="TOP"><table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" border="0">
<tr>
    <td  bgcolor="#DCDCDC" width="100%" valign="top"><tt><font color="#000000">
Author:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:&#112;&#101;&#114;&#99;&#104;&#49;&#48;&#55;&#64;&#101;&#97;&#114;&#116;&#104;&#108;&#105;&#110;&#107;&#46;&#110;&#101;&#116;?subject=What Happened to Us On Hate Raid">Perch Mackenzie</a>&nbsp;(proxy.lga.netsetter.com)<br>
Date:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;08-05-2001 10:36<br><br>
Hi There,<BR>
<BR>
I am a new probationary member with Seekers of Lore.  I went up for Plane of Hate Raid on Saturday August 04 2001.  What a mess.  Despite the fact that Wild Knights and us didn't agree on the AOE Spell and Train issue, does this mean our alliance must be broken.  After WK left, things did get better and we started to move to 2nd safe spot before i had to log 7 hours later.  With 53 folks up ther i had a hard time even being able to hit a mob with all the melee myself.  Here is a possible solution to our problem next time we do a plane raid with this many peeps:<BR>
<BR>
1.  If more than 50 peeps, split the groups into two sections;Ex:  4 groups of 6 in each section.  Next, give each section their own space;EX:  One Section go safespot and other section go SW Corner.  Next, make a head of each Section for looting purposes.  Next, each Section Leader gets their own talk channel;EX:  Dinia will use OOC.  Asturn will use Auction.<BR>
<BR>
Good things that happen from this.<BR>
1.  Reduces trains.<BR>
2.  If section dies, then there is remaining section to assist.<BR>
3.  A melee can actually hit the mob instead of fight the crowd.<BR>
4.  2 leaders can control 2 smaller groups better than 1 leader controlling 1 large group.<BR>
<BR>
Final Word:<BR>
I am new to Seekers of Lore, but I will call a spade a spade.  The Wild Knights do need to be familiar with the loot table system if it is OUR RAID and we should be familiar with their loot system if it is THIER RAID.  That is fair.  It is unfair to blame Wild Knights for the AOE Spell Casting.  There were too many peeps in one area. That was the problem.  It was difficult and frustrating for the melee to target mobs and chanters to mez mobs.  On my own behalf I apologize to the Wild Knights for any hard feelings about raid.  I hope we can keep our alliance.  They are good people.  That is the final word.<BR>
</font></tt></td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
